Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction, credit for 38 days time served. Defendant may have release to the Day Reporting Center and release to participate in educational/vocational programming at the House of Correction. Defendant may NOT have work release unless employed at the time of revocation.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs and alcohol;
2) Participate in a cognitive thinking program;
3) Random urine screens;
4) Participate in vocational programming full time;
5) Perform 30 hours of community service. All hours to be completed within the first 6 months of probation. 
6) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds and earnings. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
signed Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant William D Berry in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant William D Berry in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder on behalf of Kimberly Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for return on warrant. Discussion regarding the defendant's non-appearance at the last court date. Arguments heard as to bail. Court ordered cash bail set in the amount of $1,000.00 with turnover to Justice Point monitoring with the following conditions:
- Maintain absolute sobriety;
-No driving;
Defense counsel has received discovery but not an offer from the State. Parties anticipate a resolution in this matter and defense counsel requested a projected plea and sentencing date. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 9, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
